When you use the keyword internal it is not exposed to other jars and not available for usage outside the jar but can be used inside the jar by another package. Here the internal package is extending `com.myPackage.component` further down the hierarchy. As quote by [Jon Skeet](https://stackoverflow.com/users/22656/jon-skeet) `Packages are not hierarchical as far as the compiler is concerned - the &quot;hierarchy&quot; is just human pattern matching for organization, effectively.` That is what I mean by extending the package further.

